HEADWORD: Burlap
<hw>Bur"lap</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A coarse fabric,
made of jute or hemp, used for bagging; also, a finer variety of similar
material, used for curtains, etc.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>burlaps</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

